               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origPlace>
                        <placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0165DSM">Dabra Sāhl Qǝddus Mikāʾel Bet Maḵāʿ</placeName>
                     </origPlace>
                     <origDate notBefore="1800" notAfter="1867">The manuscript was bought and
                        donated to the church during the rule of <persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10102Webeha">daǧǧāzmāč Wǝbe Ḫāyla Māryām</persName>
                        (1835-1867) (s. Additio 1).</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>According to Additio 1 ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat
                     donated the Ms. (s. also donation note <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>). The
                     names in the original donation note were washed out (s. Additio 2); other
                     persons are mentioned in supplication formulas: Wangelāwit (s. <locus target="#84ra">84ra</locus>, 84rb, 92vb, 94va), 
                     Habta Māryām (<locus target="#86vb">86vb</locus>), 
                     Masqal Kǝbrā (<locus target="#87va">87va</locus>). Elsewhere, a few other names are crudely written,
                     interlineally, by a different hand; Kidāna Māryām in supplication formulas
                     (<locus target="#20va">20va</locus>, 25va, 40vb, 50va, 50va, 85va); Naftālem
                     (<locus target="#84vb">84vb</locus>, 86ra, 86vb, 87v-88r). Possibly, these
                     Kidāna Māryām and Naftālem are linked to ʾabuna Gabra Ḥǝywat.</provenance>
               </history>
